      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_PrepareForNextManualBillingPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to manage the transition between billing periods within a manual billing system. It performs operations on the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ManualBillingApplicationTimeFrame",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table to update the status of billing periods, specifically marking the current processing period as completed and preparing for the next billing cycle."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving basic SQL operations such as DELETE, SELECT, and UPDATE. It does not include complex logic, conditional branching, or iterative processes, making it relatively simple to understand and maintain."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
